<paragraph blockId="46.[670,1199,894,1763]" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">
IDENTIFICATION: Numerous authors have provided descriptions and measurements of 
<taxonomicName box="[670,933,1015,1038]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Desmodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rotundus">
<emphasis box="[670,933,1015,1038]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">Desmodus rotundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including 
<bibRefCitation author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978), Swanepoel and 
<bibRefCitation author="Genoways, H. H. &amp; S. L. Williams" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Carnegie Mus." pageId="46" pageNumber="46" pagination="323 - 335" part="48" refId="ref93773" refString="Genoways, H. H., and S. L. Williams 1979. Records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname. Ann. Carnegie Mus. 48: 323 - 335." title="Records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname" type="journal article" year="1979">Genoways (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hall, E. R." box="[768,911,1075,1098]" journalOrPublisher="New York: Wiley and Sons" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" refId="ref94782" refString="Hall, E. R. 1981. Mammals of North America, 2 nd ed. New York: Wiley and Sons." title="Mammals of North America, 2 nd ed" type="book" year="1981">Hall (1981)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Koopman, K. F." box="[930,1138,1075,1098]" editor="A. M. Greenhall &amp; U. Schmidt" journalOrPublisher="Boca Raton, FL: CRC Press" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" refId="ref96628" refString="1988. Systematics and distribution. In A. M. Greenhall and U. Schmidt (eds.), Natural history of vampire bats: 1 - 17. Boca Raton, FL: CRC Press." title="Systematics and distribution" type="book" volumeTitle="Natural history of vampire bats: 1" year="1988">Koopman (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Greenhall, A. M. &amp; G. Joermann &amp; U. Schmidt" bookContentInfo="6 pp." box="[670,949,1105,1128]" journalOrPublisher="Mamm. Species 202" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" refId="ref94642" refString="Greenhall, A. M., G. Joermann, and U. Schmidt 1983. Desmodus rotundus. Mamm. Species 202: 6 pp." title="Desmodus rotundus" type="book" year="1983">Greenhall et al. (1983)</bibRefCitation>
. Two subspecies are recognized by some authors (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Hall, E. R." box="[1068,1192,1135,1158]" journalOrPublisher="New York: Wiley and Sons" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" refId="ref94782" refString="Hall, E. R. 1981. Mammals of North America, 2 nd ed. New York: Wiley and Sons." title="Mammals of North America, 2 nd ed" type="book" year="1981">Hall, 1981</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones, J. K., Jr. &amp; D. C. Carter" box="[670,969,1166,1189]" editor="Baker, J. K. &amp; Jones, Jr. &amp; D. C. Carter" journalOrPublisher="Biology of bats of the New World family Phyllostomidae, pt. 1: 7 - 38. Spec. Publ. Mus. Texas Tech Univ." pageId="46" pageNumber="46" part="10" refId="ref96048" refString="Jones, J. K., Jr., and D. C. Carter 1976. Annotated checklist with keys to subfamilies and genera. In R. J. Baker, J. K. Jones, Jr., and D. C. Carter (eds.), Biology of bats of the New World family Phyllostomidae, pt. 1: 7 - 38. Spec. Publ. Mus. Texas Tech Univ. 10." title="Annotated checklist with keys to subfamilies and genera" type="journal volume" volumeTitle="R. J" year="1976">Jones and Carter, 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Greenhall, A. M. &amp; G. Joermann &amp; U. Schmidt" bookContentInfo="6 pp." journalOrPublisher="Mamm. Species 202" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" refId="ref94642" refString="Greenhall, A. M., G. Joermann, and U. Schmidt 1983. Desmodus rotundus. Mamm. Species 202: 6 pp." title="Desmodus rotundus" type="book" year="1983">Greenhall et al., 1983</bibRefCitation>
): 
<taxonomicName authority="Geoffroy (1810)" authorityName="Geoffroy" authorityYear="1810" box="[758,1143,1196,1219]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Desmodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="rotundus">
<emphasis box="[758,779,1196,1219]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[799,810,1196,1219]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">r</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[830,933,1196,1219]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">rotundus</emphasis>
Geoffroy (1810)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wagner (1840)" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1840" box="[670,1029,1226,1249]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Desmodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="murinus">
<emphasis box="[670,691,1226,1249]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[709,720,1226,1249]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">r</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[739,834,1226,1249]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">murinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner, J. A." box="[846,1029,1226,1249]" journalOrPublisher="Supplementband, 1 Abt. Die Affen und Flederthiere. [First part of Wagner's supplement to Schreber's multivolume work.] Erlangen: Expedition des Schreber'schen saugthier- und des Esper'schen Schmetterlingswerkes, etc" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" refId="ref102129" refString="Wagner, J. A. 1840. Die Saugthiere in Abbildungen nach der Natur, mit Beschreibungen von Dr. Johann Christian Daniel von Schreber. Supplementband, 1 Abt. Die Affen und Flederthiere. [First part of Wagner's supplement to Schreber's multivolume work.] Erlangen: Expedition des Schreber'schen saugthier- und des Esper'schen Schmetterlingswerkes, etc." title="Die Saugthiere in Abbildungen nach der Natur, mit Beschreibungen von Dr. Johann Christian Daniel von Schreber" type="book" year="1840">Wagner (1840)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Whereas 
<bibRefCitation author="Cabrera, A." bookContentInfo="307 pp." journalOrPublisher="Rev. Museo Argent. Cienc. Nat. '' Bernardino Rivadavia' ' (Cienc. Zool.) 4" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" refId="ref91973" refString="Cabrera, A. 1958. Catalogo de los mamiferos de America del Sur. Rev. Museo Argent. Cienc. Nat. '' Bernardino Rivadavia' ' (Cienc. Zool.) 4 (1): 307 pp." title="Catalogo de los mamiferos de America del Sur" type="book" year="1958">Cabrera (1958)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." box="[892,1064,1256,1279]" journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978) referred all South American specimens to 
<taxonomicName authority=", Jones and Carter (1976)" authorityName="Jones and Carter" authorityYear="1976" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Desmodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="rotundus">
<emphasis box="[1143,1164,1286,1309]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1179,1190,1286,1309]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">r</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[670,781,1316,1339]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">rotundus</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones, J. K., Jr. &amp; D. C. Carter" box="[807,1136,1316,1339]" editor="Baker, J. K. &amp; Jones, Jr. &amp; D. C. Carter" journalOrPublisher="Biology of bats of the New World family Phyllostomidae, pt. 1: 7 - 38. Spec. Publ. Mus. Texas Tech Univ." pageId="46" pageNumber="46" part="10" refId="ref96048" refString="Jones, J. K., Jr., and D. C. Carter 1976. Annotated checklist with keys to subfamilies and genera. In R. J. Baker, J. K. Jones, Jr., and D. C. Carter (eds.), Biology of bats of the New World family Phyllostomidae, pt. 1: 7 - 38. Spec. Publ. Mus. Texas Tech Univ. 10." title="Annotated checklist with keys to subfamilies and genera" type="journal volume" volumeTitle="R. J" year="1976">Jones and Carter (1976)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Greenhall, A. M. &amp; G. Joermann &amp; U. Schmidt" bookContentInfo="6 pp." box="[670,942,1346,1369]" journalOrPublisher="Mamm. Species 202" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" refId="ref94642" refString="Greenhall, A. M., G. Joermann, and U. Schmidt 1983. Desmodus rotundus. Mamm. Species 202: 6 pp." title="Desmodus rotundus" type="book" year="1983">Greenhall et al. (1983)</bibRefCitation>
gave the range of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1840" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Desmodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="murinus">
<emphasis box="[1169,1190,1347,1370]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[670,681,1377,1400]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">r</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[698,793,1377,1400]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">murinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as extending from Mexico southward throughout northern South America to Amazonia. Unfortunately, no data were presented to support either the differentiation of these two forms or their geographic distribution. Although we are aware of some potentially significant geographic variation within 
<taxonomicName box="[757,900,1588,1611]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Desmodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rotundus">
<emphasis box="[757,778,1588,1611]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[797,900,1588,1611]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">rotundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is not currently possible to distinguish subspecies in the absence of a comprehensive revision.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[670,1199,894,1763]" lastBlockId="47.[128,657,214,443]" lastPageId="47" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">
Our material of 
<taxonomicName box="[902,1139,1679,1702]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Desmodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rotundus">
<emphasis box="[902,1139,1679,1702]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="46">Desmodus rotundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
corresponds closely to that described from Surinam by 
<bibRefCitation author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." box="[801,976,1740,1763]" journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="46" pageNumber="46" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978) and from French Guiana by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brosset, A. &amp; P. Charles-Dominique" journalOrPublisher="Mammalia" pageId="47" pageNumber="47" pagination="509 - 559" part="54" refId="ref91807" refString="Brosset, A., and P. Charles-Dominique 1990. The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach. Mammalia 54: 509 - 559." title="The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach" type="journal article" year="1990">Brosset and Charles­Dominique (1990)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="47.[128,657,214,443]" pageId="47" pageNumber="47">
FIELD OBSERVATIONS: All of the five 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Desmodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rotundus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="47">Desmodus rotundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
we captured at Paracou were taken in ground­level mistnets. Two individuals were taken in well­drained primary forest, two in swampy primary forest, and one in a manmade clearing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
